<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="465" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,151,1868]" pageId="17" pageNumber="465">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1663,1688]" pageId="17" pageNumber="465">Etymology.</emphasis>
From the Latin “ 
<emphasis box="[533,648,1664,1688]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="465">maculatus</emphasis>
” (spotted), which refers to the distinct dorsal pale spot at the base of metasoma.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="465" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,151,1868]" pageId="17" pageNumber="465">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1735,1760]" pageId="17" pageNumber="465">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[343,577,1736,1760]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Apsilocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="465" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis box="[343,577,1736,1760]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="465">Apsilocera maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to a group of species without ornamentation on the vertex. It most closely resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[356,451,1772,1796]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Apsilocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="465" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dupla">
<emphasis box="[356,451,1772,1796]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="465">A. dupla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from which it differs in having the clypeus with one small tooth (bidentate in 
<taxonomicName box="[1325,1420,1772,1796]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Apsilocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="465" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dupla">
<emphasis box="[1325,1420,1772,1796]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="465">A. dupla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), mandible formula 
<number box="[358,372,1808,1832]" pageId="17" pageNumber="465" value="3.0">3</number>
:? 
<number box="[389,406,1808,1832]" pageId="17" pageNumber="465" value="4.0">4</number>
(
<number box="[422,438,1808,1832]" pageId="17" pageNumber="465" value="4.0">4</number>
: 
<quantity box="[442,488,1807,1832]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.016" pageId="17" pageNumber="465" unit="in" value="4.0">4 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName box="[495,590,1808,1832]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Apsilocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="465" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dupla">
<emphasis box="[495,590,1808,1832]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="465">A. dupla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation box="[615,698,1807,1832]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1926,1949]" captionTargetBox="[181,1405,193,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[181,1405,193,1905]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 30. Apsilocera spp., female, holotype, head in anterior view. 25 A. fulvipennis; 26 A. longicornis; 27 A. maculata; 28 A. obtusicristata; 29 A. palliclava; 30 A. tuberculata." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248100/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="465">
Fig. 
<number box="[667,698,1808,1832]" pageId="17" pageNumber="465" value="27.0">27</number>
</figureCitation>
), and metasoma dorsally with a large pale spot at base (no spot in 
<taxonomicName box="[151,246,1844,1868]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Apsilocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="465" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dupla">
<emphasis box="[151,246,1844,1868]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="465">A. dupla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
